title.narrative: OT2.1. ISS & Public Finance for Children (PF4C)

description.narrative: By 2020, the social protection system is further integrated and strengthened to effectively identify and respond to vulnerabilities of children to poverty and deprivation., which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Public Finance And Local Governance, Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, statutory needs based services to disadvantaged families are in place to realize the right of the child to live in caring, protective and resilient family environments.

title.narrative: By 2020, the social protection system is further integrated and strengthened to effectively identify and respond to vulnerabilitiesof children to poverty and deprivation.

description.narrative: UNICEF’s advocacy and key role in mobilizing resources and convening key partners around constructive policy dialogue contributed to the advancement of shock-responsive and integrated social protection systems in close collaboration with the Government, with a particular focus on mitigating the effects of poverty, deprivation and dual crises on children, women and vulnerable families. UNICEF’s co-lead of the UN humanitarian cash programming sub-working group within the inter-agency response plan leveraged additional allocations by partners for Government-led cash programmes for supporting basic needs of displaced families and children. | Status:Met | As-of Date:21/01/2022
